<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-450-656  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 450 656.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Systems News  July 24 1989 n427 p3(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Export reform no boon to PCs.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Peterson, Stacey.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Even though the relaxation of federal restrictions onmicrocomputer exports to non-Communist countries is not expectedto result in higher sales, the computer industry and governmentconsider the move a major step toward decontrol.andP;  The new ruleallows the export of AT-level machines to non-Communist countrieswithout the need for government approval.andP;  The Commerce Departmentis also proposing the removal of controls on low-end microcomputerexports to Communist countries.andP;  The proposal was presented to theCoordinating Committee on Multilateral Export Controls (COCOM),the 17-nation body that sets policies for the export ofhigh-technology products to the Eastern bloc.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     MicrocomputersExportGovernment RegulationCoordinating Committee for Multilateral Export ControlsInternational Trade.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>